  <brief_title>Drainage Seton With Flap Versus EAS Preserving Seton in Treatment of Transsphincteric Anal Fistula</brief_title>
  <official_title>Drainage Seton Around the External Anal Sphincter With Mucosal Advancement Flap Versus External Anal Sphincter Preserving Seton in Treatment of Trans-sphincteric Anal Fistula</official_title>
