  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with high trans-sphincteric anal fistula will be randomized to one of two equal
      group: group 1 will have drainage seton with mucosal advancement flap and group 2 will
      undergo external anal sphincter sparing seton
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
